<p class="page" id="a3960040">[Page 40]</p>
<p>Bgde. left Gully about 9pm. &amp; bivouaced some 3 miles back but were scattered by shellfire about midnight &amp; made for trenches at hand<strike> y</strike> where we slept till morning. One man was killed within 6 yds of where I lay &amp; all I knew was the feeling of a shower of dirt. Never heard the report I had well dosed myself with Rum before retiring &amp; was surely doped &amp; dead sleepy with same.</p>
<p>6th &ndash; Sunday.<br/>Bgde reviewed by Gen. Birdwood midday. Making up Coy Casualty</p>
